WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:09.840 --> 00:00:13.840
So it looks as if small groups of men, women and children

00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:20.520
made that first push into America about 13,500 years ago.

00:00:20.600 --> 00:00:22.880
Using their sophisticated tools,

00:00:22.880 --> 00:00:25.480
they made the most of their new home

00:00:25.480 --> 00:00:30.800
and spread right across the continent, from coast to coast.

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:38.600
Until recently, this was the version of American 
prehistory that most experts agreed on.

00:00:38.680 --> 00:00:41.320
But a new discovery here in Texas

00:00:41.320 --> 00:00:45.320
is threatening to rewrite the entire story.

00:00:56.120 --> 00:01:01.080
Archaeologist Mike Collins is a very patient man.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:10.120
For 15 years, he's been digging away

00:01:10.120 --> 00:01:12.240
in this small field near Austin,

00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:17.560
and he's found something that no one expected.

00:01:18.920 --> 00:01:21.640
So Mike, what sort of dates have you got coming out here?

00:01:21.720 --> 00:01:26.000
We have the entire prehistory of 
central Texas represented at this site.

00:01:26.080 --> 00:01:28.120
The kinds of artefacts we find

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:30.640
and the few absolute dates that we have

00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:34.040
tell us that people were here from 500 years ago

00:01:34.040 --> 00:01:37.480
back 13,500 years ago.

00:01:38.040 --> 00:01:41.800
Even more importantly, we have stuff below that.

00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:45.040
- Below Clovis. So, older than Clovis.
- Older than Clovis. Pre-Clovis.

00:01:45.240 --> 00:01:46.880
- Right.
- Right here at this site.

00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:53.160
But for years, archaeologists have thought 
that Clovis was the first culture in the Americas.

00:01:53.320 --> 00:01:55.040
Yeah, most archaeologists have thought that

00:01:55.040 --> 00:01:56.840
but there's a few of us that have known better.

00:01:57.280 --> 00:01:59.400
And over on the other side of the site,

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:00.880
you can see the Clovis level

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:02.560
and you can see artefacts below it.

00:02:02.640 --> 00:02:04.200
You want to see that?
- I'd love to see it.

00:02:04.200 --> 00:02:06.000
Let's go see it.

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:17.080
Mike, this is an incredibly deep test pit.

00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:18.640
Yes, it's a deep test pit.

00:02:18.640 --> 00:02:21.440
And we're really interested in this part of it right here.

00:02:21.440 --> 00:02:24.200
Because right through here, we get Clovis artefacts.

00:02:24.200 --> 00:02:27.200
But as we dug down, we continued to get artefacts below that

00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:31.360
for about 20 or 25 centimetres more.

00:02:31.480 --> 00:02:34.320
A nice flake here, for example, with a platform

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:37.320
and good flake scars on it.

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:41.400
We have one date from down here of 14,400 years.

00:02:41.520 --> 00:02:43.080
14,400?

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:44.240
Yeah.

00:02:44.240 --> 00:02:45.840
So that's pre-Clovis.

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:47.800
By 1,000 years.

00:02:47.880 --> 00:02:51.520
I mean, that's amazing because that makes us rethink

00:02:51.600 --> 00:02:54.240
all of our theories about early Americans.

00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:57.000
Yes, we have to rethink our paradigm.

00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:59.440
We have to come up with a new accounting

00:02:59.440 --> 00:03:01.160
of the peopling of the Americas.

00:03:01.240 --> 00:03:05.120
Mike, how sure are you about the date of these artefacts?

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:06.600
It's just one date.

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:09.480
So you need to corroborate it with further evidence.

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:11.560
And that's what we're working on.

00:03:25.160 --> 00:03:28.160
Now, we can only draw tentative conclusions

00:03:28.160 --> 00:03:29.720
from the evidence emerging here,

00:03:29.720 --> 00:03:32.520
but our grand theory

00:03:32.520 --> 00:03:35.320
about how humans first got into North America

00:03:35.320 --> 00:03:38.080
is starting to look decidedly dodgy.

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:43.680
Because if there really were people living 
here at Gault as early as Mike says they were,

00:03:43.680 --> 00:03:47.520
then there must have been another route into the Americas

00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:50.800
because the ice-free corridor wasn't open yet.

00:03:50.880 --> 00:03:53.000
But what I need is more proof.

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:56.800
And if the claims coming out 
of South America are to be believed,

00:03:56.880 --> 00:04:02.880
then they may have even earlier and more 
compelling evidence than I've seen here in Texas.

